      <example>
         <codeblock>&lt;conbody&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;If your workgroup has symbols files that are defined once for all
the books you author, you can define parameter entities for those symbols
within your SGML document. Parameter entities allow you to define an
imbed file of symbols, then reuse the same entities many times in your document.&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;example&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Entity declarations have the following formats:&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;!ENTITY symbol "text"&gt; for a text entity&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;!ENTITY name system "systemID"&gt; for a file entity&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;
 &lt;/example&gt;
 &lt;/conbody&gt;
</codeblock>
